Parliament, Monday, 28 October 2019 – The Standing Committee on Appropriations (SCOA) will tomorrow be briefed by Eskom’s Executive Board on the challenges facing the power utility. The meeting follows the unavailability of the board during an oversight visit of the committee in the Gauteng province during the week of 14 -16 October 2019, and the resolution that the board is to brief the committee by the end of October 2019. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Tuesday, 29 October 2019
	Time: 16:00
	Venue: Old Assembly Chamber ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE STANDING COMMITTEE ON APPROPRIATIONS, MR SFISO BUTHELEZI. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact: Name: Felicia Lombard
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8285
	Cell: 081 548 7011
